                },
                {
                    text: "The sky will burn at forty-five degrees, Fire approaches the great new city. Immediately a huge, scattered flame leaps up, When they want to have verification from the Normans.",
                    options: [
                        { text: "The atomic bombing of Hiroshima", correct: true },
                        { text: "The Great Fire of London", correct: false },
                        { text: "The Chernobyl disaster", correct: false },
                        { text: "The burning of Rome under Nero", correct: false }
                    ],
                    explanation: "This is often interpreted as describing the atomic bomb dropped on Hiroshima, with 'forty-five degrees' possibly referring to the latitude or the angle of the bomber's approach."
                },
                {
                    text: "The ancient work will be accomplished, And from the roof evil ruin will fall on the great man. Being dead, they will accuse an innocent of the deed, The guilty one hidden in the misty woods.",
                    options: [
                        { text: "The assassination of John F. Kennedy", correct: true },
                        { text: "The assassination of Abraham Lincoln", correct: false },
                        { text: "The execution of Louis XVI", correct: false },
                        { text: "The death of Julius Caesar", correct: false }
                    ],
                    explanation: "Many believe this quatrain predicted JFK's assassination, with conspiracy theories about a 'guilty one hidden' suggesting a second shooter."
                },
                {
                    text: "At dawn from the sun one will see a great fire, Noise and light extending towards the North: Within the earth death and cries are heard, through sword and fire he seeks to destroy.",
                    options: [
                        { text: "The Chernobyl nuclear disaster", correct: true },
